given.name: NoInputAndNoOutput
given.documentation: The example tests how requests and responses are serialized when there's no request or response payload because the operation has no input or output. While this should be rare, code generators must support this.

cases.description:
Clients must always send an empty JSON object payload for
operations with no input (that is, `{}`). While AWS service
implementations support requests with no payload or requests
that send `{}`, always sending `{}` from the client is
preferred for forward compatibility in case input is ever
added to an operation.

given.name: NoInputAndOutput
given.documentation: The example tests how requests and responses are serialized when there's no request or response payload because the operation has no input and the output is empty. While this should be rare, code generators must support this.

Compression algorithm encoding is appended to the Content-Encoding header, and the
user-provided content-encoding is NOT in the Content-Encoding header since HTTP binding
traits are ignored in the awsJson1_0 protocol.
